33/*
34 * Routines for manipulating stacks
35 */
36
37#include <stdio.h>
38#include <assert.h>
39#include <stdlib.h>
40
41#include "stack.h"
42#include "memory.h"
43
44#define STACK_SEEDSIZE 5
45
46struct stk {
47 int st_nument;
48 int st_top;
49 void **st_data;
50
51 void (*st_free)(void *);
52};
53
54stk_t *
55stack_new(void (*freep)(void *))
56{
57 stk_t *sp;
58
59 sp = xmalloc(sizeof (stk_t));
60 sp->st_nument = STACK_SEEDSIZE;
61 sp->st_top = -1;
62 sp->st_data = xmalloc(sizeof (void *) * sp->st_nument);
63 sp->st_free = freep;
64
65 return (sp);
66}
67
68void
69stack_free(stk_t *sp)
70{
71 int i;
72
73 if (sp->st_free) {
74 for (i = 0; i <= sp->st_top; i++)
75 sp->st_free(sp->st_data[i]);
76 }
77 free(sp->st_data);
78 free(sp);
79}
80
81void *
82stack_pop(stk_t *sp)
83{
84 assert(sp->st_top >= 0);
85
86 return (sp->st_data[sp->st_top--]);
87}
88
89void *
90stack_peek(stk_t *sp)
91{
92 if (sp->st_top == -1)
93 return (NULL);
94
95 return (sp->st_data[sp->st_top]);
96}
97
98void
99stack_push(stk_t *sp, void *data)
100{
101 sp->st_top++;
102
103 if (sp->st_top == sp->st_nument) {
104 sp->st_nument += STACK_SEEDSIZE;
105 sp->st_data = xrealloc(sp->st_data,
106 sizeof (void *) * sp->st_nument);
107 }
108
109 sp->st_data[sp->st_top] = data;
110}
111
112int
113stack_level(stk_t *sp)
114{
115 return (sp->st_top + 1);
116}
